		<tr>
			<td>
				
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    EQ Gathering III Review</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:xanthus@everlore.com">Xanthus</a></b></font>
					<font face="verdana" size="1">[7/10/2000 7:45:46 PM]</font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
					
				<P>
The Las Vegas EverQuest gathering was scheduled for July 9th, on Sunday. Most attendee’s arrived in Vegas on a Friday or Saturday so that they could enjoy a night out on the town, and of course hit the casinos! <P>

There was a Saturday get-together dinner, which was an informal event that took place at the Planet Hollywood. People gathered here to have a few drinks and meet some fellow EverQuesters before the big event the next day. This event was almost a mini gathering in itself with over 150 people including quite a few from <a href="http://www.verant.com/">Verant Interactive</a> in attendance. The food was great, and the atmosphere excellent. Around 9:00PM, the dinner came to a close and people headed off to hit the casinos or get some sleep for the gathering the next day. <P>

Sleep, In Vegas? *Laugh*. Not likely!<P>

*Skipping drunken night out in casinos*<P>

Sunday morning was a hard one for many including us. Looking at the tired crowd of people and the few hung over attendee’s gathering at the door, we reconsidered whether Vegas was really a good place for an event this early in the morning. So many distractions, so many things to do! Check-in and registration was around 9:00AM. We were already there set up with our stack of Everlore shirts and still trying to get our netcam online. Unfortunately, Stryder had the login password for our ISP and was passed out in the hotel room from the night before so we had to wait a few hours before we could start doing a live feed.<P>

The room was soon filled with *tired* fans chatting away before the initial announcements. Cindy Archuleta, the event coordinator made the introduction announcements to get things started. This event had the most Verant attendance in the history of the gatherings. There was an estimate of over 15 Verant attendees present. Brad Mcquaid did the initial Verant introductions.  Later on, he made the first public announcement of the development for a second EverQuest expansion, shocking everyone. We quickly wrote up a report and sent it out 15 minutes later. Unfortunately, they were unable to demonstrate their upcoming game, Sovereign. We found out that they are redesigning their graphics engine among other things. The expected beta of the game will be the first or second quarter of 2001.<P>

After all the announcements were made, the gathering officially started. A train like I have never seen stormed Nick Kremenek’s table for their t-shirts and posters. Nick Kremenek has been to every gathering doing the event artwork for the posters and t-shirts.  These can be found on his website <a href="http://www.dreamforger.com/">here</a>. There were a few other special guests at the event such as <a href="http://www.toyvault.com">Toy Vault</a> displaying their upcoming EverQuest action figures. Those should be available on the market this September. The guys from <a href="http://www.rpgwear.com">RPGWear</a> were on site selling their “Got Sow?” T-Shirts. Those can still be bought online from their website.<P>

The next few hours were basically a general chat and get-to-know-you sessions with everyone. The hot topic of discussion of course was the new continent, Velious. According to EQ history and some pre-beta maps we’ve seen, Velious is the last remaining continent. In the history of EverQuest, Veeshan, Crystalline Dragon and ruler of the Plane of Sky deposited her blood onto the frozen continent of Velious, where life began. <P>

Lunch consisted of ham sandwiches and potato salad. During lunch our netcam went down! We were having an ftp problem and unable to resolve the situation remotely. We ended up using an alternative website to host our netcam image, and managed to get it working in our netcam description area. <P>

At the finish of lunch around 1:30PM, Cindy gave out some prizes for winners of a drawing and started the next event. The Real Life Quest consisted of a group finding various items from a list, which were picked from the game. People went all out during this quest going far and wide for items in hopes of winning the event. One very young and enthusiastic EverQuest fan actually tore out his baby tooth and donated it as a quest component! The real life quest was a complete success and awards were given out to the winning group. <P>

The last event before dinner was the Trivia Quest. This event was organized in groups as well.  There were all sorts of questions such as listing the Gods of Norrath or listing all the game zones in EverQuest. Prizes were also awarded to the winning group of this event.<P>

By around 6:00PM, we were starving! Nick and I almost ordered a pizza to the convention room before dinner.  It’s hard work lounging in a chair, chatting with folks all day. :) We heard rumors that Verant had a ‘tuning meeting’ over dinner but that is still unconfirmed. <P>

Brad McQuaid and Jeff Butler dropped by to chew the fat and generously agreed to chat online with the fans in Everlore’s IRC lounge.  First discussed was the latest news in the EverQuest community – Velious. Many questions were answered from the level range of Velious to character model changes. That information can be found on our <a href="http://www.everlore.com/articles.asp?id=172999">chat log here</a>. One thing not noted is that there will be 12 new zones in the expansion and that there will be a Barbarian starting city located someplace in Velious. The expected release date will be this December.  Gordon “Abashi” and Baelish from Caster’s Realm also took their turns chatting with the folks on Everlore.  While Xomiach and I were talking with Brad and Jeff they were cautious not to say too much about the new continent.  While Jeff was careful about leaking any specifics he wasn’t hesitant about his enthusiasm for the end product.  Jeff put a cap on the on the whole conversation by grinning and saying “Velious is going to kick ass.” <P>
 
After leaving the Everlore area Verant crew were corralled around a table near us to do an autographing session. Lines soon formed as fans rushed to get their posters and various items signed. We didn’t hesitate to get our giant Everlore banner signed.  But to do it we had to enlist the aid of a helpful Necromancer with a real-life staff (At this point internally we are in disagreement as to whether the staff was supposed to be a staff of discord, staff of writhing or staff of undead legions) to get our banner down.  We were offered up to 1,000$ for the banner, but I think we will want to hold onto it for now :). Things started to wind down as final prizes were given out and the event was brought to a formal close. We had took some final pictures with a few from the Verant crew then had to head off. The Las Vegas Gathering brought over 450 people, close to double the last event.  There’s been some talk of EverQuest Gathering IV, it will most likely be located on the East Coast (Personally I’m voting for Florida.  Hehe, its good to travel on Everlore’s dime :) ). We will keep you posted on that in the near future! Pictures for the event can be found in the link below:<P>
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/eqevent3/default.asp?mode=list&page=1"><font size="4">Show me the pictures!</font></a></font>
<P>

Editorial by Xanthus<BR>
Webmaster, <a href="http://www.everlore.com">Everlore</a>
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td></tr>
